<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
Simon: in 2.3  (old CVS) <p>
The sandworm queen didn't have armor to steal, and didn't drop it when killed. 
</p>
<p>
This was with preserve mode on, and was my first time going at level 30 in the worm-type dungeon. So I don't expect the armor to be absent for the usual bug (with preserve off). 
</p>
<p>
This may have to do with the fact I used to have 2.2.7 on my machine. I cleared that up and got guardians to drop their item once, but with a new character the trouble came back! 
</p>
<p>
...or was the sandworm queen armor removed from the game?? 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./SoulWynd">SoulWynd</a>: I did the quest with 2.3 CVS and the worm queen dropped the armor normaly so I'm not sure what may have caused that. 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./MassimilianoMarangio">MassimilianoMarangio</a>: Did you play with Preserve mode off (see under =, birth options)? 
</p>
<p>
Simon: I now always play with preserve on, and I explicitely stated that was my only visit on the level so this can't be a case of non-preserve. It wasn't there to begin with. I'll try other guardians later and update you... 
</p>
